Before you start coding 

(follow the steps below to run the project)
step 1:
docker-compose -f backend/docker-compose.yml build --no-cache
docker-compose -f backend/docker-compose.yml up

step 2: cd mobile (always in mobile)

step 3: npx react-native run-android

docker down:
docker-compose -f backend/docker-compose.yml down -v


====================================================================================
(backend postgresql)

step 1: psql -h localhost -p 5432 -U scdf_username -d scdf_db
		password:scdf_password

-------------if have error (due to same port docker & pgadmin port 5432)--------

step 2: netstat -ano | findstr :5432


step 3: tasklist /FI "PID eq 7824"
		tasklist /FI "PID eq 21212"


step 4: Stop or disable the service/program occupying port 5432

		If either is a native PostgreSQL service, stop it to free the port:

		Open Services (press Win+R, type services.msc)

		Find PostgreSQL service(s)

		Stop and disable it temporarily


step 5: docker-compose down -v
		docker-compose up --build

step 6: psql -h localhost -p 5432 -U scdf_username -d scdf_db
		password:scdf_password




